205.4765.  Unlawful acts regarding computers: Generally.   

1.  Except as otherwise provided in subsection 6, a person who knowingly, willfully and without 
authorization:  
(a)  Modifies;  
(b)  Damages;  
(c)  Destroys;  
(d)  Discloses;  
(e)  Uses;  
(f)  Transfers;  
(g)  Conceals;  
(h)  Takes;  
(i)  Retains possession of;  
(j)  Copies;  
(k)  Obtains or attempts to obtain access to, permits access to or causes to be accessed; or  
(l)  Enters,  
data, a program or any supporting documents which exist inside or outside a computer, system 
or network is guilty of a misdemeanor.  
2.  Except as otherwise provided in subsection 6, a person who knowingly, willfully and without 
authorization:  
(a)  Modifies ; 
(b)  Destroys;  
(c)  Uses;

